  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nLet's take for example a `BeaconState` with 100K validators. Below are rough memory numbers:\r\n- SSZ serialized state is about 13Mb\r\n- Number of backing tree nodes is ~2M (1M - `BranchNode` + 1M - `LeafNode`) \r\n- Backing tree consumes ~170Mb of heap \r\n- Additionally ~200Mb is softly referenced cached backing tree `View`s\r\n\r\nMost of space (> 95% ) is occupied by the `BeaconState.validators` list which is mostly immutable. \r\nLoading states from the `Store` makes things even more dramatic: a lot of duplicated backing subtrees can occupy gigabytes of heap and often lead to OOM ",
